               <msContents>
                  <summary>I) Daily Office Prayers and Litanies (fols. 3ra-20va)&#xD;
II) Śǝrʿatä qǝddase “Ordinary of the Mass” (fols. 20va-50rb)&#xD;
III) Anaphoras (fols. 50rb-133ra)&#xD;
III-1) Anaphora of the Apostles (fols. 50rb-63va)&#xD;
III-2) Anaphora of Our Lord Jesus Christ (fols. 63va-67va)&#xD;
III-3) Anaphora of St John the Son of Thunder (fols. 67va-77va)&#xD;
III-4) Anaphora of Our Lady by St Cyriacus of Behnesa (fols. 77va-87rb)&#xD;
III-5) Anaphora of the 318 Orthodox Fathers of Nicaea (fols. 87rb-94ra)&#xD;
III-6) Anaphora of St John Chrysostom (fols. 94ra-98vb)&#xD;
III-7) Anaphora of St Epiphanius of Cyprus (fols. 98vb-104vb)&#xD;
III-8) Anaphora of St Athanasius of Alexandria (fols. 104vb-113va)&#xD;
III-9) Anaphora of St Gregory (“Hosanna-liturgy of St Gregory”) (fols. 113va-119rb)&#xD;
III-10) Anaphora of St Jacob of Serug (fols. 119rb-124vb)&#xD;
III-11) Anaphora of St Dioscorus of Alexandria (fols. 124vb-126vb)&#xD;
III-12) Anaphora of St Cyril of Alexandria (fols. 126vb-133ra)&#xD;
&#xD;
Additio 1; Colophon.</summary>
