                     <origDate notBefore="1872" notAfter="1889">ff. 17rb, 37rb, 57va-vb, 78ra: Yoḥannǝs is mentioned as the reigning monarch, Ṗeṭros and salāma as the Patriarchs (?) and ʾAtnatewos as the Metropolitan. f. 78rb, etc.: Ṗeṭros is mentioned as the Metropolitan.&#xD;
Yoḥannǝs IV was Emperor of Ethiopia in 1872-89. ʾAtnatewos was Metropolitan of Ethiopia in 1869-76. Ṗeṭros IV was Metropolitan of Ethiopia from 1881 to ca. 1889. The mention of ʾabba salāma as Patriarch of Alexandria is difficult to account for. The Ms. can most safely be dated to the reign of Yoḥannǝs IV.</origDate>
